cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with error detection in learner writing using neural sequence labeling approach, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses different training strategies and auxiliary objectives to improve the performance of the neural model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a model that can learn general-purpose compositional features. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural models and their optimization. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on software engineering specifically, but rather on improving the performance of a neural model for error detection.
